                    Residential/commercial real estate development company seeking a virtual Revit Designer/BIM Technician for work in a challenging, dynamic, entrepreneurial and fast paced company in ongoing mixed-use high rise US projects.



Work hours are United States New York City Time, Eastern Time.



Professional, team-player position requires a positive, self-starting attitude, demonstrated organizational ability, high attention to detail and the ability to work independently and with minimal supervision on challenging assignments with strict deadlines in a fast paced environment.



Job description includes:



Using Revit, Navisworks, ArchiCAD and Vectorworks for BIM modeling and coordination of architectural and engineering drawings for high rise Multifamily and mixed use projects (min 5 years experience required).



Creating detailed 3D models, generating accurate construction drawings, and managing project workflows and quality control through BIM.



Setting up templates, families and schedules, as well as collaborating across disciplines using Revit work-sharing tools.



Using Navisworks to coordinate large models and detect trade conflicts.



Using CAD software, such as AutoCAD and SolidWorks, to prepare and revise technical drawings



Working with engineers and other professionals to produce and revise drawings that meet their specifications;



Writing related technical documents such as material lists and cost estimates and specification summaries;



Ensuring that all drawings are accurate and meet industry standards;



Updating existing drawings as new information becomes available;



Creating and maintaining electronic Dropbox filing systems of City Building Codes; and



Other functions in support of the company and its executives.



Job requirements include:



Direct high rise Multifamily portfolio experience;

Flexible hours;

Strong communication skills and strong written and verbal English ability (additional Spanish language skills a plus);

Extreme attention to detail;

Exceptional organizational skills;

Expert ability in Microsoft excel, word and powerpoint;

Professional growth mindset;

Being an organized, pro-active, independent-minded team player who is energetic and self-motivated;

Strong time management skills;

Being a critical thinker who thrives under pressure and in a fast-paced environment;

Integrity and discretion and the ability to work with strict confidentiality;

University/College degree; and

Minimum 5 years verifiable experience in high rise multifamily projects in the United States.



As part of the interview process applicant will be asked to conduct and lead a live, walk-through demonstration of a mixed-use complex development schedule to demonstrate applicant's aptitude and knowledge of scheduling and working on a mixed-use project in the United States.



The position is a Full Time position with the Company and applicant should not intend to hold other employment for other employers while working for the Company.
